<body>
    <h1 class="latest-bike-head">Upcoming Bikes</h1>
    <div class="TWupcoming-container">
        <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-image">
            <img src="@Model.ImageFolderURL" alt="@Model.UpcomingBikeName" title="@Model.UpcomingBikeName" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='@Url.Content("~/images/twowheeler/default.jpg")';" />
            <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-text">
                <h2>@Model.UpcomingBikeName</h2>
                <p><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i>  @Model.ExpectedLaunchDate</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-content">
            <h2>About @Model.UpcomingBikeName</h2>
            @* <p>@Html.Raw(@Upbike.UpcomingBikeDetails.Replace("\n", "<br>"))</p> *@
            <h3 class="subheading">Newly Launched Oben Rorr EZ Electric Bike in India</h3>
            <p>The Oben Rorr EZ, a new electric bike aimed at urban commuters, was launched in India with a starting price of ₹89,999. This entry-level model offers three battery options with a range of up to 175 km per charge, a top speed of 95 km/h, and multiple color choices.</p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Details on the Oben Rorr EZ Electric Bike</h3>
            <p>Oben Electric, a Bengaluru-based electric vehicle company, has introduced the Rorr EZ electric bike to the Indian market as an affordable option for city riders. Starting at an introductory price of ₹89,999 (ex-showroom), the Rorr EZ is available with three battery capacities—<span class="font-weight-700">2.6 kWh, 3.4 kWh, and 4.4 kWh</span>. The Rorr EZ achieves a top speed of 95 km/h and offers three <span class="font-weight-700">driving modes (Eco, City, Havoc)</span>, tailored for varied riding styles.</p>
            <p>With the 4.4 kWh battery, the Rorr EZ can achieve a maximum range of 140 km in Eco mode, 110 km in City mode, and 90 km in Havoc mode. The charging time depends on the battery variant; the standard charger takes 4 to 7 hours, while a fast charger can restore up to 80% charge within 45 minutes to 2 hours.</p>
            <p>The bike also includes modern features such as geo-fencing, anti-theft systems, and a comprehensive LED dashboard. Design-wise, it closely resembles its sibling, the standard Oben Rorr, and is available in multiple colors, including Flux Grey, Surge Cyan, and Photon White. Oben Electric offers a warranty of 3 years/50,000 km, extendable to 5 years/75,000 km.</p>
            <p>The Rorr EZ will go up against similar commuter focused electric bikes in the market such as the Revolt RV1.</p>
            <h3 class="subheading">Specifications:</h3>
            <p class="font-weight-700">Price: ₹89,999 - ₹1,09,999 (ex-showroom, India)</p>
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <span class="font-weight-700">Battery options:</span> 2.6 kWh, 3.4 kWh, 4.4 kWh
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="font-weight-700">Range:</span> Up to 140 km (Eco mode)
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="font-weight-700">Top Speed:</span> 95 km/h
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="font-weight-700">Charging Time:</span> 4 to 7 hours (standard), 45 minutes to 2 hours (fast charger)
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="font-weight-700">Motor Power:</span> 7.5 kW, 52 Nm torque
                </li>
             </ol>
        </div>
    </div>
    }
    <!-- Bike 1 -->
    <h1 class="for-h1">Explore Latest & Upcoming Bikes</h1>
    <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-row">
        @foreach (var allUpbike in ViewBag.allupcomingbike)
        {
            <a href="/@allUpbike.ImageURL" style="text-decoration:none;">
                <div class="upcoming-bikes-details-card">
                    <div class="upcoming-bikes-all-image">
                        <img src="@allUpbike.ImageFolderURL" alt="@allUpbike.UpcomingBikeName" title="@allUpbike.UpcomingBikeName" onerror="this.onerror=null; this.src='@Url.Content("~/images/twowheeler/default.jpg")';" />
                    </div>

                    <div class="upcoming-allbikes-details-content">
                        <h2>@Truncate(@allUpbike.UpcomingBikeName, 22)</h2>
                        <p><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i>  @allUpbike.ExpectedLaunchDate</p>
                        <a href="/@allUpbike.ImageURL" class="details-button" style="text-decoration:none;">View Details</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </a>
        }
    </div>
</body>